The article highlights statements from various members of Congress, cabinet members, business leaders, associations, labor unions, and state and local officials regarding President Trump's executive order establishing the National Council for the American Worker and the American Workforce Policy Advisory Board. Many of the individuals and organizations express support for the executive order, emphasizing the importance of workforce development and training to address the skills gap and prepare workers for the jobs of the 21st century. They also pledge to invest in training programs and provide enhanced career opportunities for American workers.